Industry prices continue to rise
The prices of domestic industrial sales in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - informs the Central Institute of Hungarian Statistics.
The export sales prices of the industry reported in July 2008 were higher than 1.1%, compared to the previous year decreased by 3.9%.
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were higher by 0.7% than in the previous month and by 3.2 % compared to one year ago.
The prices of domestic industrial sales compared to the previous month have only increased by 0.1%.
The domestic sales prices of the processing sector have also risen to a minimum of 0.1% compared to July.
The highest price increase in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoe processing sector (2.8%), especially the bags and belts with 4.6% and the production of shoes with 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastics and chemicals caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the chemicals and products sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electrical instruments and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum extent in the wood processing industry (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry there was an increase in prices between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the field of electricity, gas, steam and water supply, prices increased by 0.3% in August in domestic industrial sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the increase in gas price by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared in 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the manufacturing industries, the largest increases were in the oil processing sector (32.4%).
In the field of the manufacture of products resulting from the processing of metals, the price increase was 13.2%, 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco representing a decisive weight.
A decrease in prices occurred in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of instruments and electrical machinery (0.3%).
In the other sectors of the processing industry, the pace of price increases varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the processing industry in the past year prices have risen by 10.2%.
The electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector prices exceeded 18.7% last year.
In domestic sales among target groups of sectors, the highest monthly price increase occurred in August in sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods prices rose by 0.3%, in the energy sector and in subsequent use prices did not change compared to those of the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, higher prices were observed in the energy sector and subsequent use (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
The prices of industrial export sales calculated in florins increased in August by 1.1% compared to the previous month, compared in 12 months decreased by 3.9%.
The Hungarian flower in the course of a month has weakened compared to the euro of 1.7%, compared to the dollar of 7.1%, compared with August 2007 has strengthened by 7.5% compared to the euro and by 15.9% compared to the dollar.
